# <%@meta name="title"%>

This report benchmark the performance of <%=fcnname%>() against alternative methods.

## Alternative methods

* apply() + sum()
* rowSums()


## Data
```r
<%=withCapture({
<%@include file="R/random-matrices.R"%>
data <- rmatrices(mode="integer")
})%>
```

## Results

<% for (ii in seq_along(data)) { %>
<%
dataLabel <- names(data)[ii]
message(dataLabel)
X <- data[[dataLabel]]
gc()
%>
### <%=dataLabel%> matrix

```r
<%=withCapture({
X <- data[[.dataLabel.]]
stats <- microbenchmark(
 rowCounts   = rowCounts(X, value=42, na.rm=FALSE),
 "apply+sum" = apply(X, MARGIN=1L, FUN=function(x) sum(x == 42, na.rm=FALSE)),
 rowSums     = rowSums(X == 42, na.rm=FALSE),
 unit = "ms"
)
})%>
```

<% benchmarkResults(stats, tags=dataLabel) %>

<%
# Sanity checks
Y <- list(
 rowCounts   = rowCounts(X, value=42, na.rm=FALSE),
 "apply+sum" = apply(X, MARGIN=1L, FUN=function(x) sum(x == 42, na.rm=FALSE)),
 rowSums     = rowSums(X == 42, na.rm=FALSE)
)
lapply(Y, FUN=function(x) stopifnot(isTRUE(all.equal(x, Y[[1]]))))
%>

<% } # for (ii ...) %>


